  "body": "I was on a private chain and one of the nodes got stuck and kept getting this error:\n\n`0618 13:36:39.085722    6775 chain_manager.go:801] Bad block #25326 (d4d024e532c47afa8257d70e9d94145316a02e4866f515adf460fb43467256a9)\nI0618 13:36:39.085772    6775 chain_manager.go:802] invalid merkle root. received=7d7d803dd4af4609b34ee6449c32fea46f2ad38e21912c116c734d67fb92ef9e got=c9c32232f34874cf666548c41c1fc780011033022c8645c94ce49c8ddfd85bea\nI0618 13:36:39.086020    6775 downloader.go:224] Synchronisation failed: block downloading canceled (requested)`\n\nI even tried removing all its peers and connecting it to just my node (which had all proper blocks) and it still kept giving that error whilst trying to sync after being off a few hours.  \n\nl eventually just nuked its chain and let it start syncing from scratch and it worked.\n",
